---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import SiteNav from "../components/SiteNav.astro";
import SiteFooter from "../components/SiteFooter.astro";
import { SITE } from "../data/site";
---
<Layout title="Getting Started with Hal - Install and Run Your First Loop" description="A quickstart path for installing Hal and running the first PRD-driven coding loop." path="/getting-started">
  <SiteNav />
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="page-container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Quickstart</p>
      <h1>Getting started with Hal</h1>
      <p>Use a small, reviewable feature to verify the loop: initialize, plan, convert, validate, run, and inspect the result.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="page-section">
    <div class="page-container prose">
      <h2>1. Install Hal</h2>
      <pre><code>{SITE.installCommand}</code></pre>
      <h2>2. Initialize a repository</h2>
      <pre><code>hal init</code></pre>
      <p>This creates the local Hal workflow files used by the loop.</p>
      <h2>3. Plan a small requirement</h2>
      <pre><code>hal plan "add a dark mode toggle with system preference detection"</code></pre>
      <p>Keep the first task narrow enough to review in one sitting.</p>
      <h2>4. Convert, validate, and run</h2>
      <pre><code>{`hal convert
hal validate
hal run`}</code></pre>
      <h2>5. Review before merging</h2>
      <p>Inspect changed files, commits, test output, reports, and any remaining stories. Hal structures autonomous work, but the human still owns acceptance.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <SiteFooter />
</Layout>
